			<tr><td colspan="2">
				<div class="postbody">
				I have to disagree, those statements do not show he is blaming whites.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">He castigated some blacks, saying that they cannot simply blame whites for problems such as teen pregnancy and high school dropout rates....."For me there is a time ... when we have to turn the mirror around," he said. "Because for me it is almost analgesic to talk about what the white man is doing against us. And it keeps a person frozen in their seat, it keeps you frozen in your hole you're sitting in."</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This is a fact, there are black people who do this.  He is saying you cant blame whites for these problems.  The method of blaming whites for any and all social ills, while failing to see your own faults that play an incredibly large role in why you are stuck in the position you are is basically a placebo.
<br />

<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Cosby also said he wasn't concerned that some whites took his comments and turned them "against our people."</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Why be concerned about making statements that are first and foremost true?  Seriously all that's said here is that if someone out there wants to use his statements to launch an attack on the black community, then he doesn't care.
<br />

<br />
Just my opinion but I think 'reading between the lines' has lead to a false conclusion about what this man is saying.<br />
